Diagnosis. Differs from all consubgeners by the distinct rod-like process ( rp ) below promere’s apex (
Figs 14 a–c
). Opisthomere’s (
Figs 14 a–b, 14 d
) posterior process ( pp ) long, only overpassed by the anterior solenomere process ( asp ).

Anterior ridge (
ap
) well-developed in all species (except for 

M. hercules
(Verhoeff, 
1900
))

. Apical humps (
ah
and 
ph
) more or less developed (hardly detected in 

M. hercules

). Solenomere with a short, finger-formed posterior process (
psp
) and a usually longer, also finger-formed anterior process (
asp
).
